This Privacy Policy governs access and use of the Services, as defined under the Terms of Use (hereinafter referred to as
“Terms”
) on the electronic platforms, including the mobile application and/ or website, known as
“Delta Exchange India”
(hereinafter referred to as
“Platform”
). The Services (as defined in Terms) are being provided through the Platform and are operated by Excelium Technologies Private Limited (hereinafter referred to as
“Excelium”
), a company registered under the Companies Act, 2013. The underlying technology in the Platform is owned by Protocol Labs Pte Limited, a private company registered under the laws of the Republic of Singapore, which has licensed Excelium to operate and provide Services on the Platform. As explained in the Terms, there may be different versions or features of the Platform where the Services are provided to the user. Capitalised terms used but not defined herein will have same meaning as ascribed to it in the Terms.
The purpose of this privacy policy (
“Privacy Policy”
) is to enable you to understand what personal information of yours is collected, how and when we might use or share your information, and how you can correct inaccuracies in the information. Our Privacy Policy is incorporated as a part of the Terms. By registering or otherwise using our Platform, you hereby agree to the use, collection, and disclosure of the data/information we collect in accordance with this Privacy Policy. For the purposes of this Privacy Policy,
“we”
,
“us”
, or
“our”
,
“Company”
,
“Excelium”
shall refer to Excelium Technologies Private Limited and
“user”
,
“you”
, or
“your”
shall refer to you. We will adhere by the laws in place that create offences for unauthorized actions against computer systems and data. We may deny your access to our Services and/or Platform as per the conditions set out in the Terms and this Privacy Policy.
The Privacy Policy applies to all who sign up for Services in the Platform including, but not limited to the website, mobile-based application, or any other sources. You do not have the obligation to provide any information, including sensitive personal information or any other information to us. Notwithstanding the foregoing, you will not be able to obtain our Services on the Platform if you do not provide information that is stated in this Privacy Policy. If you are using/accessing this Platform it will be seen as an explicit consent of your agreement and acknowledgement of this Privacy Policy. We have also published our Privacy Policy on our Platform and the Service shall be governed in conjunction with the Terms specified therein.
