to enforce legal rights against you;
for any other purpose with your consent.
3.2.
Identity Verification and due diligence:
While using your Account and our Service you hereby declare and represent that you are a resident of India under the applicable laws of India. We will require identity verification and other screening procedures with respect to you or the transactions associated with Your User Account as per our ‘
Client Due Diligence Programme
’ as provided below. These verification and screening procedures may include, without limitation, checking the information you provide to us with any governmental authority. We retain the right to not provide Services/ suspend Your user Account in case we identify any defect in the identity verification and/or the due diligence. Your identity verification or Your KMPs’, directors’ or partners’ verification may be undertaken by the following methods:
offline verification under the Aadhaar (Targeted Delivery of Financial and other Subsidies, Benefits And Services) Act, 2016 (“
Aadhaar Act
”);
; or
any valid documents or modes of identification as notified by the Government of India from time to time.
3.2.1.
If you are an individual, you would be required to submit the following documents to us:
Aadhaar number, where you decide to submit the Aadhaar number voluntarily to us or you provide the proof of possession of Aadhaar number where offline verification can be carried out; or you provide the proof of possession of Aadhaar number where offline verification cannot be carried out;
PAN or the equivalent e-document thereof or Form No. 60 as defined in Income-tax Rules, 1962. If you do not submit the PAN.
3.2.2.
If you are a company, you would be required to submit the following documents (or equivalent e-documents) to us:
Certificate of incorporation;
Memorandum of association and articles of association;
PAN;
names of the KMPs and/or directors who would be accessing the Account, Platform or any of our Services on behalf of the company, along with the relevant information of such KMPs or directors as prescribed under Section 3.2.1;
registered office and the principal place of business, if they are different
documents required for individuals as set out above relating to Beneficial Owner, managers, officers or employees, as the case may be, holding an attorney to transact on your behalf.
3.2.3.
If you are a partnership/limited liability partnership (“
LLP
”), the partnership is required to submit the following documents (or equivalent e-documents) to the Exchange:
Certificate of registration;
Partnership Deed;
PAN;
names of all the partners and the relevant identification details of such partners as prescribed under Section 3.2.1.
address of the registered office, and the principal place of its business, if they are different;
documents required for individuals as set out above relating to Beneficial Owner, managers, officers or employees, as the case may be, holding an attorney to transact on its behalf.
3.2.4.
You may be required to provide us with certain other personal and sensitive personal information from time to time, including, but not limited to:
your name;
address;
telephone number;
email address;
date of birth;
passport number;
photograph;
a resolution from the board of directors and power of attorney granted to your managers, officers or employees, as the case may be to transact on your behalf (if you are a company);
registration certificate (if you are a partnership firm/LLP);
trust deed (if you are a trust); and
any other information as may be required.
3.2.5.
You hereby explicitly consent for us to, directly or through a third party, make any inquiries as mandated under the relevant law or what we consider necessary to verify your identity including your Aadhaar details. You hereby confirm that you will assist any third party in carrying out the verification including offline verification as provided under the Aadhaar Act. By accepting the conditions in these Terms as well as those specified in the Privacy Policy, you hereby give your “explicit consent” to collect, store, process, disclose and safeguard Your Information, including your KYC details, Aadhaar (including Masked Aadhaar) details and/or protect against fraud, including but not limited to:
query identity information contained in public reports (e.g., your name, address, past addresses, or date of birth);
query account information associated with your linked bank account (e.g., name or account balance); and
take action we reasonably deem necessary based on the results of such inquiries and reports.
3.2.6.
We would be undertaking subsequent identity verification again when you carry out:
any transaction ; or
any international money transfer operations.
3.2.7.
In case of certain specified transactions i.e., where the cash deposit or withdrawal, transaction in foreign exchange, high value import or remittance, exceeds the specified limit as prescribed by the Government of India or where there is a high risk of money laundering or terrorist financing, we would be required to carry out enhanced due diligence prior to the commencement of each such specified transaction, without which such transaction would not be permitted to be carried out. Such enhanced due diligence measures would include:
undertaking your identity verification before such transaction as specified  above;
taking additional steps to examine your ownership and financial position including obtaining information with respect to the source of funds wherein we may categorise users as low, medium, or high risk based on our assessment in the identity verification and due diligence process; and
recording the purpose behind conducting the transaction and the intended nature of the relationship of the parties to the transaction.
3.2.8.
The information collected by us while applying enhanced due diligence measures as stated above will be maintained for a period of 5 years from the date of transaction.
3.3.
Responsibility for Account Activities:
You will be bound by, and hereby authorize us to accept and rely on, any agreements, instructions, orders, authorizations and any other actions made, provided or taken by anyone who has accessed or used Your User Account regardless of whether the access is authorized or unauthorized. Upon receipt of written notice from you that the security of Your User Account has been compromised, we will take reasonable steps to protect Your User Account, including, for example, to cease to allow actions initiated using any compromised account passwords, in the event such actions are not already completed. We shall, under no circumstance, shall be liable for any loss incurred by you by any unauthorised use of Your User Account.
3.4.
Maintenance of Records:
We will be maintaining a record of transactions in a manner enabling us to reconstruct individual transactions and records of documents evidencing your/ Beneficial Owner’s identity and account files and business correspondence relating to you.
We shall maintain records in relation to the following transactions for at least 5 (five) years from the date of each such transaction:
(i) cash transactions of a value exceeding INR 10,00,000 (Indian Rupees Ten Lakhs) or its equivalent in foreign currency;
(ii) series of cash transactions where individually each transaction is valued below INR 10,00,000 (Indian Rupees Ten Lakhs) or its equivalent in foreign currency, but the monthly aggregate value of such transactions exceeds INR 10,00,000 (Indian Rupees Ten Lakhs);
(iii) suspicious transactions;
(iv) all cross-border wire transfers of a value of more than INR 5,00,000 (Indian Rupees Five Lakhs) or its equivalent in foreign where either the origin or destination of the funds is in India.
We shall maintain a record of documents evidencing your/ Beneficial Owner’s identity as well as account files and business correspondence relating to you for a period of 5 (five) years after the business relationship has ended.
3.5.
We will use and retain Your Information for such periods as necessary to comply with any applicable laws, discharge our legal obligations, resolving disputes, record keeping and to enforce our rights and remedies including enforcement of the Terms and this Privacy Policy.
3.6.
Customer Acceptance Policy:
We do not open Accounts, allow access to our Platform nor avail our Services to those users who are register with anonymously or with a fictitious and/or benami name.
We do not open Accounts, allow access to our Platform nor avail our Services to those users for whom we cannot complete the identity verification and due diligence  process, either due to non-cooperation by the user or non-reliability of the documents/information furnished by the user.
Pursuant to clause (b) of Section 3.6, the user shall not have an Account, have access to our Platform nor avail our Services until such identity verification and due diligence process has been completed by the us.
We will not open Account for those users who intend to open a joint account with another individual(s), a body corporate, or any other going concern. You hereby declare that the Account shall solely be operated, controlled, and used by you. We reserve the right to either suspend or terminate your Account pursuant to the procedures established under Section 15 of the Terms.
Notwithstanding anything contained in clause (d) of Section 3.6 shall not apply to the authorised representatives operating Accounts(s), using our Platform or availing our Services(s) on behalf of a company or partnership provided such authorised representatives have fulfilled the identity verification and due diligence requirement specified in Sections 3.2 and 3.3 in the Privacy Policy and the Terms respectively.
We reserve the right not carry our identity verification and due diligence where we have reason to believe that the user is engaging in money laundering or terrorist financing and that carrying out identity verification and verification will tip-off of such users. Further, in these situations we reserve the right to inform the concerned law enforcement agency(ies) under the Applicable Laws, including but not limited to the concerned departments under the Ministry of Home Affairs, Ministry of Finance and Reserve Bank of India.
